1
00:00:05,052 --> 00:00:09,560
Subtitle edited by <font color="#ffff00">- Aorion -</font>
"Cinderella 2015" ^ (Run time 01:40:59)

2
00:00:48,705 --> 00:00:50,405
FAIRY GODMOTHER:
Once upon a time,

3
00:00:50,438 --> 00:00:53,747
there was a girl
called Ella.

4
00:00:54,701 --> 00:00:56,977
And she saw the world
not always as it was,

5
00:00:57,002 --> 00:01:02,260
but as perhaps it could be,
with just a little bit of magic.

6
00:01:04,931 --> 00:01:06,403
Ah, my darling!

7
00:01:06,428 --> 00:01:09,604
FAIRY GODMOTHER:
To her mother and father,
she was a princess.

8
00:01:09,629 --> 00:01:13,179
True, she had no title,
nor crown, nor castle,

9
00:01:13,204 --> 00:01:16,441
but she was the ruler
of her own little kingdom,

10
00:01:16,466 --> 00:01:20,300
whose borders were the house
and meadow on the forest's edge

11
00:01:20,325 --> 00:01:23,306
where her people
had lived for generations.

12
00:01:24,836 --> 00:01:26,887
With Mr. Goose.

13
00:01:27,541 --> 00:01:30,041
and all their animal family.

14
00:01:31,217 --> 00:01:32,435
Hello, there.

15
00:01:32,460 --> 00:01:34,042
What do you think
you're doing?

16
00:01:34,067 --> 00:01:36,068
Let the little ones
have their share.

17
00:01:36,093 --> 00:01:38,811
We don't want you getting
an upset stomach.

18
00:01:38,889 --> 00:01:39,767
<font color="#b39f84">Gus-Gus: (Found my snack.)</font>

19
00:01:39,792 --> 00:01:40,710
Oh, Gus-Gus,

20
00:01:40,735 --> 00:01:43,098
you're a house mouse,
not a garden mouse.

21
00:01:43,123 --> 00:01:44,752
Isn't he, Jacqueline?

22
00:01:44,777 --> 00:01:47,441
And you mustn't eat
Mr. Goose's food.
- <font color="#b39f84">(Hungry.)</font>

23
00:01:47,466 --> 00:01:48,656
Isn't that right, Mummy?

24
00:01:48,681 --> 00:01:50,946
Do you still believe
that they understand you?

25
00:01:50,971 --> 00:01:52,324
Don't they, Mother?

26
00:01:52,349 --> 00:01:54,138
Oh, yes.

27
00:01:54,176 --> 00:01:56,465
I believe that animals listen
and speak to us

28
00:01:56,496 --> 00:01:58,190
if we only have
the ear for it.

29
00:01:58,215 --> 00:01:59,985
<font color="#b39f84">- Gus-Gus: (Well, you're right.)
- Matida: (And she could.)</font>

30
00:02:00,010 --> 00:02:01,610
That's how we learn
to look after them.

31
00:02:01,643 --> 00:02:03,097
Who looks after us?

32
00:02:03,122 --> 00:02:05,451
Fairy godmothers, of course.

33
00:02:05,476 --> 00:02:07,062
And do you believe in them?

34
00:02:07,087 --> 00:02:08,414
I believe in everything.

35
00:02:08,439 --> 00:02:11,096
Then I believe
in everything, too.

36
00:02:13,186 --> 00:02:15,038
FAIRY GODMOTHER:
Her father was a merchant

37
00:02:15,063 --> 00:02:16,236
who went abroad

38
00:02:16,261 --> 00:02:20,073
and brought tribute back from
all of Ella's subject lands.

39
00:02:20,098 --> 00:02:22,119
Ella!

40
00:02:22,144 --> 00:02:25,724
Where are my girls,
my beautiful girls?

41
00:02:26,912 --> 00:02:29,415
Where are my darlings?

42
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:32,027
FAIRY GODMOTHER:  Ella missed
him terribly when he was away.

43
00:02:32,052 --> 00:02:34,069
But she knew
he would always return.

44
00:02:34,094 --> 00:02:36,212
- ELLA'S FATHER: There she is!
- Papa, welcome home!

45
00:02:36,237 --> 00:02:38,378
ELLA'S FATHER:
How are you?

46
00:02:38,564 --> 00:02:40,190
You've grown!

47
00:02:40,215 --> 00:02:41,435
Look at you.

48
00:02:41,460 --> 00:02:42,976
Haven't you, now?

49
00:02:43,001 --> 00:02:44,647
- MAN: There you go, sir.
- What was that?

50
00:02:44,672 --> 00:02:46,554
Oh, this?

51
00:02:46,584 --> 00:02:48,718
I found it hanging
on a tree.

52
00:02:48,746 --> 00:02:50,370
I think

53
00:02:50,395 --> 00:02:53,215
there may be something inside.

54
00:02:58,047 --> 00:03:00,366
Oh, it's so pretty.

55
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:04,121
In French,
that is un papillon. (a butterfly)

56
00:03:04,152 --> 00:03:06,505
- Un papillon. (A butterfly)
- Un papillon! (A butterfly)

57
00:03:06,530 --> 00:03:08,679
Voulez vous danse avec moi, Mademoiselle?
(Will you dance with me, Miss)

58
00:03:08,704 --> 00:03:11,389
- S'il vous plaît.     (My pleasure)
- Merci beaucoup.  (Thank you very much)

59
00:03:11,414 --> 00:03:13,758
Ouch.
Ouch.

60
00:03:13,783 --> 00:03:15,329
You're standing
on my feet.

61
00:03:15,354 --> 00:03:16,871
- Heh-heh-heh.
- Ha-ha-ha.

62
00:03:16,896 --> 00:03:18,285
Shall we?

63
00:03:20,357 --> 00:03:22,738
Look, Mummy!
I'm dancing!

64
00:03:25,123 --> 00:03:26,603
Whee!

65
00:03:26,634 --> 00:03:27,824
Look out, 
Mr Goose.

66
00:03:27,851 --> 00:03:31,076
My darling wife.
Come here.

67
00:03:34,641 --> 00:03:36,930
Little  papillon.

68
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:40,925
FAIRY GODMOTHER:
All was just as it should be.

69
00:03:40,950 --> 00:03:44,631
They knew themselves to be the most
happy of families to live as they did

70
00:03:44,656 --> 00:03:46,599
and to love each other so.

71
00:03:46,624 --> 00:03:49,362
♪ When I am king
dilly, dilly

72
00:03:49,387 --> 00:03:52,256
♪ You shall be queen

73
00:03:52,281 --> 00:03:55,208
♪ Lavender's green
dilly, dilly

74
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:57,786
♪ Lavender's blue

75
00:03:57,811 --> 00:04:00,445
♪ You must love me
dilly, dilly

76
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:03,836
♪ For I love you ♪

77
00:04:09,119 --> 00:04:12,628
FAIRY GODMOTHER:  But sorrow
can come to any kingdom,

78
00:04:12,659 --> 00:04:15,336
no matter how happy.

79
00:04:21,419 --> 00:04:24,353
FAIRY GODMOTHER:
And so it came to Ella's home.

80
00:04:27,153 --> 00:04:28,415
DOCTOR: I'm so sorry.

81
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:30,389
ELLA'S FATHER:
Thank you, Doctor.

82
00:04:30,611 --> 00:04:33,343
This must have been
very difficult for you.

83
00:04:35,786 --> 00:04:37,352
Come.

84
00:04:37,377 --> 00:04:38,650
Ella.

85
00:04:53,088 --> 00:04:55,896
ELLA'S MOTHER:
Ella, my darling.

86
00:04:55,921 --> 00:04:58,501
I want to tell you a secret.

87
00:04:58,550 --> 00:05:00,051
A great secret

88
00:05:00,084 --> 00:05:03,807
that will see you through all
the trials that life can offer.

89
00:05:04,369 --> 00:05:06,994
You must always
remember this.

90
00:05:07,935 --> 00:05:12,087
Have courage and be kind.

91
00:05:12,356 --> 00:05:14,788
You have more kindness
in your little finger

92
00:05:14,813 --> 00:05:17,813
than most people possess
in their whole body.

93
00:05:17,838 --> 00:05:20,922
And it has power,

94
00:05:20,947 --> 00:05:23,270
more than you know.

95
00:05:24,176 --> 00:05:26,046
- And magic.
- ELLA: Magic?

96
00:05:26,071 --> 00:05:28,130
Truly.

97
00:05:28,623 --> 00:05:32,733
Have courage and be kind,
my darling.

98
00:05:33,591 --> 00:05:34,996
Will you promise me?

99
00:05:35,021 --> 00:05:36,782
I promise.

100
00:05:36,958 --> 00:05:38,403
ELLA'S MOTHER: Good.

101
00:05:38,564 --> 00:05:39,645
Good.

102
00:05:39,670 --> 00:05:41,201
And...

103
00:05:43,305 --> 00:05:47,023
I...
I must go very soon, my love.

104
00:05:48,259 --> 00:05:50,253
Please forgive me.

105
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:53,284
Of course
I forgive you.

106
00:05:59,757 --> 00:06:01,915
ELLA'S MOTHER:
I love you.

107
00:06:03,426 --> 00:06:05,616
ELLA'S FATHER:
I love you, my darling.

108
00:06:05,641 --> 00:06:07,524
ELLA'S MOTHER:
I love you.

109
00:06:22,695 --> 00:06:24,388
FAIRY GODMOTHER: Time passed,

110
00:06:24,413 --> 00:06:28,265
and pain
turned to memory.

111
00:06:39,429 --> 00:06:42,802
In her heart,
Ella stayed the same.

112
00:06:42,827 --> 00:06:46,001
For she remembered
her promise to her mother.

113
00:06:46,162 --> 00:06:49,792
Have courage,
and be kind.

114
00:06:53,430 --> 00:06:56,130
Father, however,
was much changed.

115
00:06:56,163 --> 00:06:59,086
But he hoped
for better times.

116
00:07:00,163 --> 00:07:02,528
"And thence home,

117
00:07:02,553 --> 00:07:06,064
"and my wife and I singing,
to our great content,

118
00:07:06,089 --> 00:07:08,904
"and if ever there were a man
happier in his fortunes,

119
00:07:08,929 --> 00:07:11,398
"I know him not."

120
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:14,198
Thus ends Mr. Pepys
for today.

121
00:07:14,231 --> 00:07:16,698
I do love a happy ending,
don't you?

122
00:07:16,731 --> 00:07:19,838
They're quite
my favorite sort.

123
00:07:19,965 --> 00:07:21,374
As well they should be.

124
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:23,199
Ella...

125
00:07:23,232 --> 00:07:26,428
I have come to the conclusion
that...

126
00:07:26,453 --> 00:07:28,940
 it's time,
perhaps...

127
00:07:28,965 --> 00:07:31,197
to begin a new chapter.

128
00:07:31,230 --> 00:07:32,866
Indeed, Father?

129
00:07:32,932 --> 00:07:34,886
You'll recall that some
time ago, in my travels,

130
00:07:34,911 --> 00:07:37,336
I made the acquaintance
of Sir Francis Tremaine.

131
00:07:37,361 --> 00:07:38,602
Yes.

132
00:07:38,627 --> 00:07:41,368
The Master of
the Mercer's Guild, is he not?

133
00:07:41,393 --> 00:07:42,824
Was.

134
00:07:42,849 --> 00:07:45,403
The poor man
has died, alas.

135
00:07:45,428 --> 00:07:47,174
His widow,

136
00:07:48,267 --> 00:07:50,234
an honorable woman,

137
00:07:50,267 --> 00:07:52,568
finds herself alone,

138
00:07:52,601 --> 00:07:55,141
though still in the
prime of her life.

139
00:07:57,134 --> 00:07:59,348
You're worried
about telling me.

140
00:07:59,761 --> 00:08:01,914
But you mustn't be.

141
00:08:02,387 --> 00:08:04,738
Not if it will lead
to your happiness.

142
00:08:04,763 --> 00:08:06,668
Yes.

143
00:08:06,693 --> 00:08:08,727
Happiness.

144
00:08:08,908 --> 00:08:10,209
Do you think I

145
00:08:10,234 --> 00:08:13,708
may be allowed
one last chance,

146
00:08:13,735 --> 00:08:16,830
even though I thought
such things were done with for good?

147
00:08:16,985 --> 00:08:20,045
Of course I do, Father.

148
00:08:23,235 --> 00:08:25,503
She'll merely be
your stepmother.

149
00:08:25,536 --> 00:08:28,893
And you'll have two lovely
sisters to keep you company.

150
00:08:37,447 --> 00:08:40,206
Have courage, be kind.

151
00:08:48,355 --> 00:08:51,729
ELLA'S FATHER:
Welcome, ladies. Welcome!

152
00:08:51,754 --> 00:08:54,713
ANASTASIA: She's skinny as a broomstick!
DRISELLA: And that stringy hair!

153
00:08:55,304 --> 00:08:56,568
You're very nice.

154
00:08:56,593 --> 00:08:58,473
ELLA: Welcome.
I'm so happy to meet you.

155
00:08:58,498 --> 00:09:00,424
You have
such pretty hair.

156
00:09:00,449 --> 00:09:01,975
- Thank you.
- You should have it styled.

157
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,703
Oh.
I'm sure you're right.

158
00:09:03,728 --> 00:09:05,370
- Would you like a tour of the house?
- What did she say?

159
00:09:05,395 --> 00:09:06,930
She wants to show us
around her farmhouse.

160
00:09:06,955 --> 00:09:09,927
- She's proud of it, I think.
- Do they keep animals inside?

161
00:09:13,530 --> 00:09:17,299
STEPMOTHER: How charming.
How perfectly charming.

162
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,405
Lucifer.

163
00:09:20,473 --> 00:09:21,876
FAIRY GODMOTHER:
Her stepmother-to-be

164
00:09:21,901 --> 00:09:25,166
was a woman of keen feeling
and refined taste.

165
00:09:25,191 --> 00:09:28,251
And she, too,
had known grief.

166
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:31,773
But she wore it
wonderfully well.

167
00:09:59,242 --> 00:10:02,676
You did not say your
daughter was so beautiful.

168
00:10:02,709 --> 00:10:04,723
Oh, she takes after her...

169
00:10:05,658 --> 00:10:07,380
Her mother.

170
00:10:08,543 --> 00:10:10,007
Just so.

171
00:10:10,043 --> 00:10:11,642
What does Mummy mean?
What's so charming about it?

172
00:10:11,667 --> 00:10:13,448
DRISELLA: She's lying.
That's just good manners.

173
00:10:13,473 --> 00:10:14,610
ANASTASIA:
Shut up.

174
00:10:14,643 --> 00:10:17,132
DRISELLA:
How long has your family lived here?

175
00:10:17,157 --> 00:10:18,154
Over 200 years.

176
00:10:18,179 --> 00:10:20,109
And in all that time,
they never thought to decorate?

177
00:10:20,134 --> 00:10:23,924
STEPMOTHER:
Anastasia, hush.

178
00:10:23,949 --> 00:10:26,684
They'll think
you are in earnest.

179
00:10:27,711 --> 00:10:29,078
FAIRY GODMOTHER:
Ella's stepmother,

180
00:10:29,111 --> 00:10:31,073
high-spirited lady
that she was,

181
00:10:31,098 --> 00:10:34,799
set out to restore life
and laughter to the house.

182
00:10:36,858 --> 00:10:39,791
STEPMOTHER:
Oh, you are awful, Baron.

183
00:10:41,769 --> 00:10:44,732
BARON:
Ah, fortune favors me again.

184
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:52,189
- ELLA: Well,
<font color="#b39f84">- Jacqueline: (Oh, she comes.)</font>

185
00:10:52,214 --> 00:10:54,178
look who's
having a party of their own.

186
00:10:54,217 --> 00:10:58,986
Jacqueline, Teddy, Matilda,
greedy Gus-Gus.
<font color="#b39f84">- Gus-Gus:  (I've got a yum yum)</font>

187
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,487
Uh-oh.

188
00:11:00,512 --> 00:11:01,813
<font color="#b39f84">Gus-Gus: (Oh, oh. It's a cat.)</font>

189
00:11:01,838 --> 00:11:04,485
Just...
what...

190
00:11:04,510 --> 00:11:07,699
Yes, what do you think
you're up to, Lucifer?

191
00:11:07,724 --> 00:11:11,528
Jacqueline is my guest,
and the eating of guests is not allowed.

192
00:11:11,553 --> 00:11:12,856
<font color="#b39f84">- Teddy: I'll hold on to it.
- Gus-Gus: No, no.</font>

193
00:11:12,881 --> 00:11:13,958
Go on, now.

194
00:11:13,983 --> 00:11:15,823
You've plenty of cat
food to keep you happy.

195
00:11:15,848 --> 00:11:17,018
<font color="#b39f84">Jacqueline: (Or put it to sleep.)</font>

196
00:11:17,090 --> 00:11:19,009
We ladies must help
one another.

197
00:11:19,034 --> 00:11:20,509
<font color="#b39f84">Jacqueline: (Oh, and I thank you.)</font>

198
00:11:23,982 --> 00:11:25,674
You're missing the party.

199
00:11:25,699 --> 00:11:28,485
Oh, I imagine it's much
like all the other ones.

200
00:11:29,590 --> 00:11:31,382
And I'm leaving
first thing, El.

201
00:11:31,415 --> 00:11:32,897
No. But you're...

202
00:11:32,922 --> 00:11:35,508
You're hardly back
from the last trip.

203
00:11:36,715 --> 00:11:38,016
Do you have to go?

204
00:11:38,049 --> 00:11:40,380
It's just a few months,
my darling.

205
00:11:42,682 --> 00:11:44,750
What would you like me
to bring you home from abroad?

206
00:11:44,783 --> 00:11:46,059
You know, your sisters...

207
00:11:46,084 --> 00:11:48,550
uh, stepsisters,
have asked for

208
00:11:48,583 --> 00:11:51,760
parasols and lace.
What...

209
00:11:51,950 --> 00:11:53,758
What will you have?

210
00:11:54,517 --> 00:11:59,159
Bring me the first branch
your shoulder brushes on your journey.

211
00:11:59,184 --> 00:12:01,785
That's a curious request.

212
00:12:01,818 --> 00:12:03,451
Well, you'll have
to take it with you

213
00:12:03,484 --> 00:12:05,110
on your way...

214
00:12:05,135 --> 00:12:07,808
and think of me
when you look at it.

215
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:12,046
And when you bring it back,
it means that you'll be with it.

216
00:12:13,018 --> 00:12:15,631
And that's
what I really want.

217
00:12:16,152 --> 00:12:18,486
For you to come back.

218
00:12:18,519 --> 00:12:20,646
No matter what.

219
00:12:22,885 --> 00:12:24,978
ELLA'S FATHER: I will.

220
00:12:26,986 --> 00:12:30,464
Ella, while I'm away,

221
00:12:30,489 --> 00:12:32,853
I want you to be good
to your stepmother

222
00:12:32,886 --> 00:12:35,294
and stepsisters,
even though they may be...

223
00:12:35,319 --> 00:12:38,326
trying...
 at times.

224
00:12:38,843 --> 00:12:40,800
- I promise.
- Thank you.

225
00:12:40,879 --> 00:12:44,305
I always leave
a part of me behind, Ella.

226
00:12:44,643 --> 00:12:46,696
Remember that.

227
00:12:46,721 --> 00:12:52,195
And your mother's here, too,
though you see her not.

228
00:12:52,220 --> 00:12:55,280
She's the very heart
of this place.

229
00:12:55,395 --> 00:12:57,363
And that's why we must
cherish this house,

230
00:12:57,389 --> 00:12:59,938
always, for her.

231
00:13:02,355 --> 00:13:04,582
I miss her.

232
00:13:05,188 --> 00:13:07,266
Do you?

233
00:13:08,355 --> 00:13:10,323
Very much.

234
00:13:23,423 --> 00:13:25,751
ANASTASIA: Remember the lace!
I simply must have it!

235
00:13:25,776 --> 00:13:26,990
DRISELLA:
And my parasol!

236
00:13:27,023 --> 00:13:29,054
For my complexion!

237
00:13:29,079 --> 00:13:32,344
That means skin,
if you don't know!

238
00:13:34,691 --> 00:13:36,227
ELLA: Bye!

239
00:13:36,257 --> 00:13:37,957
ELLA'S FATHER:
Bye, Ella!

240
00:13:37,990 --> 00:13:39,058
ELLA:
I love you!

241
00:13:39,091 --> 00:13:41,246
ELLA'S FATHER:
I love you, too!

242
00:13:43,919 --> 00:13:45,749
ELLA: Bye!

243
00:14:06,126 --> 00:14:08,225
STEPMOTHER:
Ella, dear.

244
00:14:16,327 --> 00:14:19,325
Now, now.
Mustn't blub.

245
00:14:20,327 --> 00:14:21,494
Yes, Stepmother.

246
00:14:21,527 --> 00:14:23,744
Oh, you needn't
call me that.

247
00:14:24,427 --> 00:14:26,109
"Madam" will do.

248
